Instructions to run the program.

There is a single class called "ForestFireModel.java". There's also a compiled program as "ForestFireModel.class". 

Make sure java is installed in your system. 

1. Unzip the assignment folder.
2. Navigate into the assignment folder using command prompt. 
3. Type in command prompt "javac ForestFireModel.java"
4. The program would be compiled.
5. Type in command prompt "java ForestFireModel"
6. Program will execute.
7. Enter all the probabilities to see the result.
8. At the end the program will print the results as well as write them to a file called "Results.txt", which you can find in the same assignment folder.
9. There's also a screenshot and sample results file included in the assignment.


if you need any help feel free to contact via email.
